What you need to know:

On Thursday, the team stepped up its preparations for the match with 18 local-based players taking part in a double training session at the Moi International Sports Center, KasaraniMulee insists his charges will not underrate Comoros, who lead Group ‘G’ of 2021 Afcon qualifiers with four points after edging Togo and drawing with EgyptUnattached winger Ayub Timbe Masika, Egypt-based Cliff Nyakeya and Kaizer Chiefs midfielder Anthony Akumu are the first batch of foreign-based players expected to link up with the team